race.comment: ZIVA BALE (5) turned spotting a big start finishing seventh (25.96) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Looks the one to beat on her best form. NEVERMIND (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 22.51 beating Diva's Rose. Must be included in calculations. HAPPY BUDDHA (2) jumped well from a low draw and lead for much way to score when third (22.57) at Shepparton in a Grade 5 over 390m. Racing well and deserves a win. MIA COCO (3) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish.
